I"3<h2 id="acknowledging-the-osg-consortium">Acknowledging the OSG Consortium</h2>

<p>Papers, presentations, and other publications that feature research that benefited from the <a href="/services/open_science_pool.html">Open Science Pool</a> resources, services or expertise should cite the following two articles:</p>

<blockquote class="bg-light pt-2 pb-1">
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>Pordes, R. et al. (2007). “The Open Science Grid”, J. Phys. Conf. Ser. 78, 012057.doi:10.1088/1742-6596/78/1/012057.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Sfiligoi, I., Bradley, D. C., Holzman, B., Mhashilkar, P., Padhi, S. and Wurthwein, F. (2009). “The Pilot Way to Grid Resources Using glideinWMS”, 2009 WRI World Congress on Computer Science and Information Engineering, Vol. 2, pp. 428–432. doi:10.1109/CSIE.2009.950.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</blockquote>

<p>and include in the text the following acknowledgement:</p>

<blockquote class="bg-light pt-2 pb-1">
  <p>This research was done using services provided by the OSG Consortium [1,2], which is supported by the National Science Foundation awards #2030508 and #1836650.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>For your convenience, <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OSGConnect/connectbook/master/attachments/osg.bib">a BibTex file containing the above two references</a> has been provided.</p>
